Indian Space Research Organisation
From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
Jump to navigationJump to search
Indian Space Research Organisation
Indian Space Research Organisation Logo.svg
ISRO logo (adopted in 2002)[1][2]
Abbreviation	ISRO
Formation	15 August 1969; 50 years ago
(1962 as INCOSPAR)
Headquarters	Bengaluru, Karnataka, India
12Â°57â€²56â€³N 77Â°41â€²53â€³ECoordinates: 12Â°57â€²56â€³N 77Â°41â€²53â€³E
Administrator
K. Sivan (Chairman)[3]
Primary spaceport
Satish Dhawan Space Centre (SHAR), Sriharikota, Andhra Pradesh, India
